posts.name: Mykah
posts.cooked: You are using the CAN TalonSRX Class from the CTRE Phoenix Library. According to the JavaDoc the set() method for the TalonSRX takes in two parameters, first is a TalonSRXControlMode and the second is a double . So you need to pass both parameters. https://store.ctr-electronics.com/content/api/java/html/classcom_1_1ctre_1_1phoenix_1_1motorcontrol_1_1can_1_1_talon_s_r_x.html#aa8a9315c026864fb9754bd3379a38871

posts.name: Josh Buker
posts.cooked: Okay looks like instead of 1, you would need something like rightArm.set(TalonSRXControlMode PercentOutput, 1.0);
